  id: Extensor_digitorum_digitalis_lateralis_muscle.L
  partName: Extensor digitorum digitalis lateralis muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left extensor digitorum lateralis muscle is located on the lateral side of
    the canine forearm and assists in extending the lateral digits of the paw. Originating
    from the humerus and inserting onto the distal phalanges, this muscle contributes
    to coordinated toe extension during locomotion and weight-bearing activities.
  - It works alongside other extensor muscles to maintain proper paw alignment and
    improve stride efficiency. The muscle also supports balance and stability during
    running, turning, and jumping movements by controlling digital positioning. Proper
    muscular function ensures smooth forelimb mechanics and accurate paw placement.
